To characterize the thermal tolerance curves of the ancestor and each of the evolved lineages, an inoculum of 100 cells per mL from the middle of the logarithmic phase of growth was transferred into fresh media at 15, 20, 25, 30, 32, 35, and 40 °C. Cell count was determined daily on a flow cytometer and populations were transferred to fresh media once at each temperature during the middle of the logarithmic phase of growth, before being left to reach stationary phase. Growth rates were estimated from the abundance data using a logistic growth function:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
