Measurements of photosynthesis and respiration were made on the ancestor and all evolved lineages after 300 generations of selection when in the middle of the logarithmic phase of population growth. Net photosynthesis (NP) was measured as O2 evolution at increasing light intensities in intervals of 50 µmol−1 m−2 s−1 up to 300 µmol−1 m−2 s−1, and then in intervals of 100 µmol−1 m−2 s−1 up to 1000 µmol−1 m−2 s−1, followed by 200 µmol steps up to 2000 µmol−1 m−2 s −1. The maximum rate of light saturated photosynthesis was determined by fitting the NP data to a dynamic model of photoinhibition via nonlinear least squares regression using the methods outlined in ref. 19:3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
